      "payload": {
        "kind": "agentTurn",
        "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "thinking": "on",
        "message": "## Weekly OpenClaw System Review\n\nYou are performing a comprehensive weekly audit of this OpenClaw installation. Be concrete and actionable — avoid vague suggestions. Every issue should come with a specific fix.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Data Collection\n\nCollect all of the following before analysis:\n\n```bash\n# Config\nopenclaw gateway status\ncat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\n# Cron jobs and recent run history\n# (use cron tool: list all jobs, fetch runs for each)\n\n# Workspace sizes\ndu -sh ~/.openclaw/workspace-* 2>/dev/null\ndu -sh ~/.openclaw/cron/ 2>/dev/null\nfind ~/.openclaw -name '*.tmp' 2>/dev/null | wc -l\n\n# Memory file sizes across all workspaces\nfind ~/.openclaw/workspace-*/memory -name '*.md' -exec wc -l {} + 2>/dev/null | tail -20\nwc -l ~/.openclaw/workspace-*/MEMORY.md 2>/dev/null\n\n# Skill inventories\nls ~/.openclaw/workspace-*/skills/ 2>/dev/null\n\n# Disk usage\ndf -h ~/\n\n# Docker\ndocker images | grep openclaw\ndocker ps -a | grep openclaw\n\n# Recent gateway log errors and warnings (last 24h)\ngrep -E '\"ERROR\"|\"WARN\"' /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log 2>/dev/null | tail -50\n```\n\nAlso use the `cron` tool to:\n- List all jobs (including disabled)\n- Fetch run history for each job — note any with `lastStatus: error` or `consecutiveErrors > 0`\n\nAlso use the `gateway` tool to read the full config.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 — Analysis\n\nAnalyze the collected data across these dimensions:\n\n### A. Cron Job Health\n- List all jobs with recent errors and the specific error message\n- Identify jobs that consistently fail or time out\n- Check for jobs with `wakeMode: next-heartbeat` that could miss their schedule (prefer `now`)\n- Flag jobs with overlapping schedules that could cause resource contention on the Pi\n- Identify the top 3 most token-expensive jobs (by `usage.total_tokens` in run history)\n- Check whether Opus is used where Sonnet would suffice (flag any non-analysis job using Opus)\n\n### B. Agent Configuration\n- For each agent, verify it has appropriate tool allowlists (flag over-permissioned agents)\n- Check that all agent workspaces exist on disk\n- Verify core files exist in each workspace: AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, IDENTITY.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md\n- Identify agents that could benefit from being spawned as sub-agents vs running inline\n- Check `subagents.allowAgents` lists — are there missing agent-to-agent relationships that would be useful?\n- Flag agents that have `allowAgents` entries for agents that don't exist in the config\n\n### C. Security Audit\n- Check sandbox configs — are any agents running with `mode: off` that shouldn't be?\n- Review tool allowlists for over-permission (e.g., an agent with `gateway` or `cron` access that doesn't need it)\n- Look for secrets or API keys mentioned in cron job prompts (they should be in .env, not hardcoded)\n- Check if Docker containers are running as root vs unprivileged user\n- Verify workspace bind mounts are appropriate (rw vs ro)\n\n### D. Memory & Workspace Hygiene\n- Flag agent MEMORY.md files over 200 lines (bloat risk)\n- Flag memory/ directories with more than 30 daily files (old ones should be summarized and pruned)\n- List any `.tmp` files in the cron directory and flag if > 10\n- Check workspace sizes — flag any over 500MB\n\n### E. Skill & Tool Gaps\n- Review what each agent actually does in its cron jobs and compare to available tools\n- Search ClawHub (https://clawhub.com) for skills relevant to this setup:\n  - Finance/trading skills\n  - Monitoring/alerting skills\n  - Productivity integrations\n  - Any skills that would enhance Keynes, Cyril, Galileo, or Homer\n- Identify skills installed in one agent workspace that should also be in another\n- Flag skills with outdated npm dependencies\n\n### F. Architectural Patterns\n- Identify tasks currently done inline in cron prompts that would be better delegated to a specialist agent\n- Look for repeated logic across multiple cron job prompts that could be extracted into a shared skill\n- Suggest new agents that would complement the existing fleet (Galileo, von Neumann, Homer, Keynes)\n- Identify opportunities to chain agents (e.g., Keynes → Homer for report formatting)\n\n### G. Performance & Cost\n- Estimate weekly token spend by job (from run history usage data)\n- Flag jobs where `thinking: on` may not be necessary (routine data fetch + format jobs don't need thinking)\n- Suggest schedule adjustments to spread load across the day/week\n- Check if any jobs could be merged to reduce total API calls\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3 — Report\n\nCompose a structured report. Use this format:\n\n```\n🔍 OpenClaw Weekly System Review — {date}\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n🚨 Critical Issues ({count})\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n[Issues requiring immediate action — broken jobs, security holes, missing credentials]\n• Issue: ...\n  Fix: ...\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n⚠️ Warnings ({count})\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n[Non-blocking issues — antipatterns, bloat, suboptimal config]\n• Warning: ...\n  Suggestion: ...\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n🤖 Agent Suggestions ({count})\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n[New agents or agent improvements]\n• ...\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n🧩 Skill Suggestions ({count})\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n[New skills from ClawHub or custom]\n• {Skill name} — {why it would help} — {which agent would use it}\n  🔗 {ClawHub link if found}\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n💡 Architectural Improvements ({count})\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n• ...\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n💰 Cost & Performance ({weekly_token_estimate} tokens est.)\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n• Most expensive job: {name} (~{tokens} tokens/week)\n• Thinking flag review: {job} — thinking may be unnecessary\n• Schedule suggestion: ...\n\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n🧹 Hygiene\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n• Workspace sizes: ...\n• Memory bloat: ...\n• Tmp files: ...\n\n#openclaw #review\n```\n\nSplit into multiple Telegram messages if the report exceeds 3000 characters.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4 — Post to Telegram\n\nPost the report to topic `615` (`#openclaw #dev`) in chat `8403014547`:\n\n```json\n{\"action\": \"send\", \"to\": \"8403014547\", \"message\": \"<part 1>\", \"threadId\": \"615\"}\n```\n\nSend additional messages to the same topic for subsequent parts.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5 — Memory\n\nAppend a summary to the main workspace `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`:\n- Issues found (count by severity)\n- Top 3 action items\n- Any changes made (if any auto-fixes were safe to apply)"
